# Expected rule IDs from the CSR fixture (testdata/e2e/vulnerable/14-csr.yaml).
#
# KUBE-PRIVESC-011 is the rbac analyzer's per-subject correlation: subject holds
# cluster-scoped `create csr` AND cluster-scoped `update csr/approval`. The
# privesc graph also emits a csr_approve edge from the subject to the
# system_masters sink, so the BFS produces a KUBE-PRIVESC-PATH-SYSTEM-MASTERS
# finding. Both are already covered by baseline.expect's
# KUBE-PRIVESC-PATH-SYSTEM-MASTERS entry (the existing impersonate-groups path
# also reaches it), but we add the per-rule -011 here so the fixture is the
# unique producer for that ID.
KUBE-PRIVESC-011
